Remarks. The new species is closely related to
P.setigera
from the Philippines and Indonesia . These species can be differentiated by the following characters:

One incomplete male from BOA 0, Stn CP2327 (

P. aff. setigera

), showed a significant genetic divergence with the other specimens, 4.71% (16S rRNA) and 8.90% (ND1), suggesting the existence of an additional cryptic species. Unfortunately, the incomplete specimen prevents a complete description, and additional material is necessary in order to determine its taxonomic status.
